name: Conservancy Fairy Shrimp
overview: The females hold their eggs a ventral brood sac where they the baby Fairy shrimp emerge. The purpose of this shrimp has the a large effect to the many other organisms within the vernal pool caring and taming the algae and bacteria. These fairy shrimp have the purpose of eating, mating, then laying eggs for the next generation of fairy shrimp.
habitat: They live in the cool waters of the vernal pools of California and Oregon.
